INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'd84d491a-1542-4760-9f6a-b8c7b171fb4e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Jest Async Testing — waitFor, findBy, and Fake Timers Done Right$escape$,
  $escape$Jest's async utilities each serve a distinct role. `findBy*` queries (from Testing Library) internally call `waitFor`, polling until the element appears or timing out after 1000ms by default — use them for DOM assertions after async state updates. `waitFor` is for non-element assertions: expect a callback to stop throwing within the timeout window.

Avoid wrapping `findBy` inside `waitFor` — it's redundant and masks real errors. Also avoid `act()` wrapping around `waitFor`; Testing Library handles that internally.

For promise-based code, `resolves`/`rejects` matchers keep tests readable: `await expect(fetchUser(1)).resolves.toEqual({ id: 1 })`. Always `await` these — a missing `await` silently passes even when the promise rejects.

Fake timers need special care with async code. When using `jest.useFakeTimers()`, promises may stall because microtasks are queued behind fake macrotasks. Call `jest.runAllTimersAsync()` (Jest 29+) or flush promises explicitly with `await Promise.resolve()` between `jest.advanceTimersByTime()` calls. Always restore with `jest.useRealTimers()` in `afterEach` to prevent timer leaks across tests.$escape$,
  $escape$import { render, screen, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';

// findBy: polls until element appears (replaces waitFor + getBy)
test('loads user name', async () => {
  render(<UserProfile id={1} />);
  const name = await screen.findByText('Alice'); // built-in retry
  expect(name).toBeInTheDocument();
});

// waitFor: non-element async assertion
test('calls onSuccess after save', async () => {
  const onSuccess = jest.fn();
  render(<SaveButton onSuccess={onSuccess} />);
  userEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button'));
  await waitFor(() => expect(onSuccess).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1));
});

// Fake timers + async: flush microtasks manually
test('debounced fetch fires after 300ms', async () => {
  jest.useFakeTimers();
  const spy = jest.spyOn(api, 'search').mockResolvedValue([]);
  render(<SearchBox />);
  userEvent.type(screen.getByRole('searchbox'), 'react');
  jest.advanceTimersByTime(300);
  await Promise.resolve(); // flush pending microtasks
  expect(spy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('react');
  jest.useRealTimers();
});$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
